\begin_layout Standard
The simplest 2x2 Hamiltonian to describe the node line structure can be
 written as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
H=\big[-\epsilon_{0}+\alpha(k_{x}^{2}+k_{y}^{2}+k_{z}^{2})\big]\sigma_{z}+\beta k_{z}\sigma_{x}=\left[\begin{array}{cc}
-\epsilon_{0}+\alpha(k_{x}^{2}+k_{y}^{2}+k_{z}^{2}) & \beta k_{z}\\
\beta k_{z} & \epsilon_{0}-\alpha(k_{x}^{2}+k_{y}^{2}+k_{z}^{2})
\end{array}\right]\label{eq:}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
